<P>Go, leave me, said he, as I approached him; add not, by thy hateful presence, to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> of this moment&mdash;I thought, by dying <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> and misery together, to fly from the terrors of a reproaching conscience; but, alas! my miseries are but just beginning.</P>
<P>Oh! thou detested, wretched old man, continued he, drawing me forcibly towards him, thou art ig|norant what a task thou hast yet to perform: Go, lose not a moment, but use every method to restore that injured angel Julietta to her senses&mdash;give her back her fortune&mdash;and do thou retire to some de|sert&mdash;fast, pray, and lay upon the cold ground&mdash;years and years spent in supplication will hardly gain that pardon you so much need.&mdash;There is! there is! an hereafter&mdash;I feel it now rush on my <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> soul.&mdash;You do not know how hard it is to <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> plunge at once into eternity.&mdash;Oh! murder, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> cannot be forgiven.</P>
<P><PB N="176" REF="026108_0171_0FCFAF00A39396F8">
At that instant he expired with a groan, so hol|low, that it still <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> in <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span">.</P>
<P>I hear thee, Oh! thou <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> shade&mdash;I will obey thee.</P>
<P>Hester, continued Vellum, I have sent for you home, that you may administer comfort to Juliette&mdash;here, take this paper, and go prepare for your journey; when you are separated from me, open it; you will there find full instructions how to act&mdash;leave me, my child; I am now more composed, I may perhaps take some rest.</P>
<P>Hester gladly retired.</P>
<P>I saw from the agitation of her features, though she could not but pity the distresses of her father's mind, it was impossible for her any longer to love him.</P>
<P>That task is over, said Vellum, as she shut the door&mdash;now, what remains?&mdash;to pray for pardon.&mdash;Pardon for what?&mdash;Murder. Ah! that is <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> all; my soul is loaded with crimes.&mdash;Fraud, <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word">, oppression, are in the horrid catalogue!&mdash;the wi|dows, the fatherless children whom I have oppres|sed, will rise up in judgment against me.&mdash;Mercy&mdash;Oh! mercy just God!&mdash;but wretch that I am, did I ever shew mercy&mdash;will <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> just Creator then shew mercy to me?&mdash;No&mdash;for I thirst appear at a tribunal where every one will be rewarded accord|ing to his works.</P>
<P>Oh that I was annihilated!&mdash;that I had never lived&mdash;for the distraction of my mind is too mighty to be borne&mdash;I will not bear it&mdash;I will end my tortures&mdash;my life is in my own power; and it <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> to plunge at once into evils which <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> more dreadful than this constant terror.&mdash;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 span"> the instrument, said he, taking a pistol from <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="AELD" EXTENT="1 word"> pocket.</P>
